    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="463"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5F1/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 12, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. 1. Pittman Sub-Committee on February 11 presented to Senate Foreign Relations
                    Committee an interim report<note n="40" xml:id="d463fn40">For Senate Resolution
                        442 introduced by Senator Key Pittman of Nevada, February 11, see <hi
                            rend="italic">Congressional Record</hi>, vol. 74, pt. 5, p. 4557. The
                        resolution was reported with amendments (Senate Report 1716), considered,
                        amended, and agreed to, February 20; see <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, pt.
                        6, pp. 5498–5502.</note> recommending that the Senate advise the President
                    to <pb facs="0722" n="608" xml:id="pg_608"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Negotiate with Indian, British, French, Belgian and other Governments
                            to induce them to suspend debasement of silver currency and government
                            sales of silver;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Call an international conference to consider an agreement in regard to
                            the uses and status of silver as money under Chapter 376, Section 312,
                            Revised Statutes;</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>Negotiate with the National Government of China and with such other
                            governments “as China and the United States may consider it advisable”
                            in regard to a silver loan to China on a commodity basis.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>2. Text of report will be mailed to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
